FBIS4-13573 "drnes077_r_94008" FBIS-NES-94-077 Daily Report 20 Apr 1994 India Kashmir Governor Comments on Situation in Valley Kashmir Governor Comments on Situation in Valley BK2004063494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0435 GMT 20 Apr 94 BK2004063494 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] The Jammu and Kashmir governor, General K.V. Krishna Rao, said the security situation in the Kashmir valley has considerably improved. Addressing a meeting of senior-level officials in Jammu, he said the security forces have achieved notable successes in their drive against the militants with the increased cooperation from the people. Meanwhile, the former chief minister of the state, Dr. Farooq Abdullah, has said the solution to the Kashmir problem lies not in violence but in political discussions. He told PTI in Jammu yesterday that as the path of violence has failed in Punjab so it will in Kashmir.
